-- Facebook COO Sandberg Sells 309,807 Shares for $8.38 Million
-- B y   T i m   C u l p a n
-- 2012-12-21T05:34:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-21/facebook-coo-sandberg-sells-309-807-shares-for-8-38-million.html
Facebook Inc. (FB)  Chief Operating
Officer  Sheryl Sandberg  sold 309,807 shares, worth about $8.38
million.  The shares were sold in multiple transactions at prices
ranging from $26.75 to $27.90 apiece, Menlo Park, California-
based Facebook reported in a  filing  with the U.S. Securities and
Exchange Commission. Facebook, operator of the worldâ€™s largest
social network, closed at $27.36 on Dec. 20 and has lost 28
percent since selling shares for $38 each in an initial public
offering in May.  With the sale, Sandberg reduced her stake to about 16.5
million directly held shares and 1.8 million indirectly held
shares, according to the filing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
